parameters.description: Minimum zooplankton assimilation efficiency when phytoplankton are severely nutrient-limited (high C:N ratio, poor food quality). Represents the baseline conversion efficiency of carbon-rich but protein-poor phytoplankton biomass.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Minimum zooplankton assimilation efficiency under nutrient-limited conditions

parameters.description: Maximum zooplankton assimilation efficiency when phytoplankton are nutrient-replete (balanced C:N ratio, high food quality). Represents optimal conversion efficiency of high-quality, protein-rich phytoplankton biomass.

parameters.description: Nutrient recycling efficiency from zooplankton mortality and excretion
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Zooplankton nutrient recycling efficiency fraction

parameters.description: External nutrient input rate from upwelling, mixing, or atmospheric deposition

parameters.description: Annual mean surface light intensity (photosynthetically active radiation). This is the baseline around which seasonal variation occurs.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Annual mean surface photosynthetically active radiation intensity

parameters.description: Fractional amplitude of seasonal light variation (0 = no seasonality, 1 = light varies from 0 to 2*mean). Typical temperate ocean values are 0.3-0.5, representing ±30-50% variation around the annual mean.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Fractional amplitude of seasonal surface light variation

parameters.description: Day of year when surface light intensity reaches its maximum (phase shift for seasonal cycle). For Northern Hemisphere, typically ~172 (June 21, summer solstice). For Southern Hemisphere, use ~355 (December 21).
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Day of year when light intensity peaks (seasonal phase)

parameters.description: Half-saturation constant for light-limited phytoplankton growth (light intensity at which growth is half-maximal)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Half-saturation light intensity for phytoplankton growth

parameters.description: Background light attenuation coefficient for clear seawater (absorption and scattering by water and dissolved matter)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Background water light attenuation coefficient

parameters.description: Phytoplankton self-shading coefficient (light attenuation per unit phytoplankton biomass, representing chlorophyll absorption)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Phytoplankton-specific light attenuation coefficient

parameters.description: Mixed layer depth (depth over which phytoplankton are mixed and experience average light conditions)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Oceanic mixed layer depth

parameters.description: Temperature sensitivity of phytoplankton growth (Q10 coefficient: factor by which growth rate increases per 10°C temperature increase)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Q10 temperature coefficient for phytoplankton metabolic rates

parameters.description: Temperature sensitivity of zooplankton grazing and metabolism (Q10 coefficient: factor by which rates increase per 10°C temperature increase)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Q10 temperature coefficient for zooplankton metabolic rates

parameters.description: Temperature sensitivity of nutrient remineralization processes (Q10 coefficient: factor by which remineralization increases per 10°C temperature increase)
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Q10 temperature coefficient for bacterial remineralization rates

parameters.description: Reference temperature at which maximum rates (r_max, g_max, etc.) are defined; typical temperate ocean mixed layer temperature
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Reference temperature for rate normalization

parameters.description: Annual mean mixed layer temperature. This is the baseline around which seasonal temperature variation occurs. Typical values: tropical oceans 25-28°C, temperate oceans 10-15°C, polar oceans 0-5°C. Should be close to T_ref for consistency with rate parameter definitions.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Annual mean mixed layer temperature

parameters.description: Amplitude of seasonal temperature variation (half of annual temperature range). Represents how much temperature varies above and below T_mean. Typical values: tropical oceans 1-3°C, temperate oceans 5-10°C, polar oceans 3-8°C. Higher values create stronger seasonal forcing and more pronounced spring/fall blooms.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Amplitude of seasonal mixed layer temperature variation

parameters.description: Day of year when mixed layer temperature reaches its maximum (phase shift for seasonal temperature cycle). Due to ocean thermal inertia, temperature peaks 30-60 days after light peak. For Northern Hemisphere temperate oceans, typically ~210-230 (late July to mid-August). For Southern Hemisphere, use ~30-50 (late January to mid-February). The lag between light peak (t_phase) and temperature peak (t_phase_temp) is critical for realistic bloom dynamics.
parameters.enhanced_semantic_description: Day of year when temperature peaks (seasonal phase with thermal lag)
